# Linker Script Reference

Full spec: `docs/linker_spec.md`. Consult it for authoritative detail.

## Three-Layer Model

```
Layer 1 — linker/kernel/*.ld.in          arch-independent kernel sections
Layer 2 — arch/tricore/linker/*.ld.in    arch-specific (CSA pool, small data, prologue)
Layer 3 — <chip_dir>/memory.ld           chip-specific MEMORY block (EXTERNAL INPUT)
           <chip_dir>/bmhd.ld.in         chip boot header (optional, only if HAVE_BMHD)

build/generated.ld   ← assembled by cmake/generate_ld.py at configure time
```

**Key rule:** chip-specific things (addresses, BMHD layout) stay in Layer 3, outside
the kernel repo. Arch-specific things uniform across all chips of that arch (CSA,
small-data ABI, OUTPUT_FORMAT) live in Layer 2. Nothing arch- or chip-specific in Layer 1.

## Chip Input Contract (Layer 3)

`<chip_dir>/memory.ld` must define:

| Region | Attrs | Required |
|--------|-------|----------|
| `KERNEL_FLASH` | rx | yes |
| `KERNEL_RAM` | rwx | yes |
| `SHARED_RAM` | rwx | yes |
| `PERIPH` | rw | yes |
| `KERNEL_FLASH_NC` | rx | only if `HAVE_BMHD = 1` |

Variables: `UL_MPU_ALIGN`, `UL_KERNEL_STACK_SIZE`, `UL_ISR_STACK_SIZE`, `UL_CSA_POOL_SIZE`.
Flags: `HAVE_CSA = 1`, `HAVE_SMALL_DATA = 1`, `HAVE_BMHD = 1`.

TC27x: `UL_MPU_ALIGN = 64`, all three HAVE flags set.
QEMU:  `UL_MPU_ALIGN = 64`, `HAVE_CSA = 1`, `HAVE_SMALL_DATA = 1` (no BMHD).

## Arch Layer (Layer 2 — in repo)

`arch/tricore/linker/`:
- `prologue.ld.in` — OUTPUT_FORMAT, OUTPUT_ARCH, ENTRY
- `csa_pool.ld.in` — CSA pool (included if HAVE_CSA)
- `small_data.ld.in` — sdata/sbss + GP anchors (included if HAVE_SMALL_DATA)

## Kernel Fragments (arch-independent)

| Fragment | Region | Key exported symbols |
|----------|--------|----------------------|
| `vectors` | KERNEL_FLASH | `_ul_trap_table`, `_ul_int_table` |
| `kernel_text` | KERNEL_FLASH | `_ul_kernel_text_start/end` |
| `kernel_data` | KERNEL_RAM | `_ul_kernel_data_start/end` |
| `kernel_stacks` | KERNEL_RAM | `_ul_kernel_stack_top`, `_ul_isr_stack_top` |
| `csa_pool` (HAVE_CSA) | KERNEL_RAM | `_ul_csa_pool_start/end` |
| `small_data` (HAVE_SMALL_DATA) | KERNEL_RAM | `_small_data_` … `_small_data4_` |
| `domain_table` | KERNEL_FLASH | `_ul_domain_table_start/end` |
| `user_pool` | KERNEL_RAM | `_ul_user_pool_start/end` |

## Domain Generation Pipeline

Three layers that must stay consistent:

**1. C (compile time)** — driver declares membership and descriptor:
```c
#define UL_MODULE_NAME asclin
#include <ul/linker.h>

UL_PRIVATE static uint8_t rx_buf[512];          /* → .domain_asclin.bss  */
UL_DEFINE_DOMAIN(asclin, UL_PERM_READ | UL_PERM_WRITE | UL_PERM_USER);
```

**2. CMake (configure time)** — registers the domain name for the generator:
```cmake
ul_add_domain(NAME asclin PERMS "UL_PERM_READ | UL_PERM_WRITE | UL_PERM_USER")
```

**3. generate_ld.py** — renders `domain_data.ld.in` per domain, exporting:
- `_ul_domain_NAME_start` / `_ul_domain_NAME_end` → used by kernel MPU setup
- `_ul_domain_table_*` (from `UL_DEFINE_DOMAIN`) → scanned at boot to configure DPR ranges

## C Macro API (`include/ul/linker.h`)

- `UL_DOMAIN_BSS(name)` — place zero-init var in `.domain_name.bss`
- `UL_DOMAIN_DATA(name)` — place init var in `.domain_name.data`
- `UL_PRIVATE` — shorthand for `UL_DOMAIN_BSS(UL_MODULE_NAME)`
- `UL_PRIVATE_INIT` — shorthand for `UL_DOMAIN_DATA(UL_MODULE_NAME)`
- `UL_DEFINE_DOMAIN(name, perms)` — inject descriptor into `.domain_table`

## Alignment Rules

- `UL_MPU_ALIGN = 64` on TC27x — every domain/app section boundary must be 64-byte aligned
- Vector tables: `ALIGN(256)` — fixed by hardware BTV/BIV address field
- CSA pool: `ALIGN(64)` — one CSA frame = 64 bytes, mandatory
- Stacks: `ALIGN(8)` — TriCore ABI minimum
- Kernel text: `ALIGN(32)` — TriCore fetch unit granularity
